{"ELEPHANT":[{"def":"A mammal of the order Proboscidia, of which two living species, Elephas Indicus and E.","pos":""}],"ELEPHANTIAC":[{"def":"Affected with elephantiasis; characteristic of elephantiasis.","pos":""}],"ELEPHANTIASIS":[{"def":"A disease of the skin, in which it become enormously thickened, and is rough, hard, and fissured, like an elephant's hide.","pos":""}],"ELEPHANTINE":[{"def":"Pertaining to the elephant, or resembling an elephant (commonly, in size); hence, huge; immense; heavy; as, of elephantine proportions; an elephantine step or tread.","pos":""},{"def":"Resembling an elephant in form or appearance.","pos":""}]}